<h2>Machaut: Poetry Readings</h2>

<p>Several of Machaut's unscored poetry has been read on record.
A partial listing follows.</p>

<p>Although these poems certainly have important lyrics, there are
presently no plans to include them here.  Perhaps this will be done
over the longer term.</p>

<h3>Dame, qui weult vostre droit</h3>
<p>Listed as R16 in the standard references, but surviving without music.</p>

<ol>

<p>No known recording</p>

</ol>

<h3>La, firent mains divers acors</h3>
<p>Le Rem&egrave;de de Fortune</p>

<ol>

<li><p><b><a href="../../cds/bay8668.htm">Bayard Musique 308 668</a></b><br>
Voyage au c&oelig;ur du Moyen &Acirc;ge<br>
Machaut: Rondeaux, Ballades, Motets, Virelais...<br>
Ensemble Obsidienne - Emmanuel Bonnardot<br>
Rec.: 2020</p></li>

<li><p><b><a href="../../cds/har8825.htm">Harmonic Records H/CD
8825</a></b><br>
Machaut: Ballades, Rondeaux, Virelais, Motets<br>
Ensemble Gilles Binchois - Dominique Vellard, dir.<br>
Rec.: 1988</p></li>

<li><p><b><a href="../../cds/mir00007.htm">Mirror Music Mi 00006/00009</a>
[4 LPs, including Mi 7a (Mass) also released separately]</b><br>
Guillaume de Machaut - Le Livre Du Voir Dis &amp; La Messe de Nostre
Dame<br>
Les Menestrels, Wien &amp; Mozart-S&auml;ngerknaben, Wien - Klaus
Walter, Michel Walter &amp; Eva Brunner, dirs.<br>
Rec.: 1978</p></li>

</ol>

